.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH antimony-remove 1  "remove " 
.SH NAME
antimony\-remove \- Remove features/profiles, or reset user definitions to the default
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBantimony remove\fR [\fB\-f\fR|\fB\-\-feature\fR] [\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR] [\fB\-\-seccomp\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fINAME\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Remove features/profiles, or reset user definitions to the default
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-feature\fR
Target a feature, rather than a profile
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Do not ask for confirmation
.TP
\fB\-\-seccomp\fR
Remove the SECCOMP Database. Overrides \-\-feature
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fINAME\fR]
The name of the profile. If absent, resets profiles that are identical to the system
